<br>
She stopped before the Gates and looked around seeing this tribe had gone from here. Some tribes were nomadic, moving from place to place, but which ever way, Ardyn wished to claim these lands for a tribe of her own. <p>~Ardyn O The Wind~<BR> =¤= Amazon Goddess of Virtue =¤=<BR>=ll= Re-Incarnation of the Warrior Shaman Otere=ll=<BR>*Amazon Warrior Shamaness*<BR> "What we do in Life echoes in eternity."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a62a2a><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uardynothewind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ardyn O The Wind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#330000>(7/25/02 10:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/amznpardyn/images/jm3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Becoming an Amazon Queen</span><hr size=1> She had camped there for 30 days waiting to see if a sister would be here to claim te Lands. She walked out of her self made yurt. Dressed in Amazon Queen leathers, first day she had worn them. They belonged to Tyger once.<br>
<br>
She raised her sword to the sky.<br>
<br>
**Blessed Ancestors, I claim these Lands and Tribe for the Coyote Sisters tribe. We will honor you.**<br>
<br>
She sheathed her blade and gave an Amazon salute to the Sky. <p>~Ardyn O'the Wind~<BR> =¤= Amazon Goddess of Virtue =¤=<BR>*Amazon Warrior Shamaness*<BR> "My friends,...they have faith in you. I dont."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uyakutofthenorth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yakut of the North</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#330000>(7/25/02 10:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/thegooddochl6/images/yakut015.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Coronating a Queen</span><hr size=1> Since the original Queen was gone from here, Yakut had the authority as a Shamaness and Former Queen to coronate a Queen.<br>
<br>
Yakut rode in on her steed and tied him to a old hitching post. She approached Ardyn with a salute and slight bow.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ready?&quot;<br>
<br>
Ardyn had nodded, and with that Yakut pulled out an antler Queen headdress from her horse's saddle bag. Ardyn brought up a table and laid a doeskin blanket across the table.<br>
<br>
Yakut sprinkled waters from the creek that sperated Scynthia from Tanais Valley on the table and cloth. She laid the headdress down on the table and set up a few candles. With a simple wave of her wand the candles lite up.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;A queen is a chalice. Let us fill you with visions of our history, fragments of a time before we were Amazons,<br>
when cannibals slaughtered our men, and warriors like the great Samsara called on the shaman for a savior from the future, an Atmah . . . the first Cyane&quot;<br>
<br>
From her saddle bag, Yakut pulled out a silver chalice made specially for this event. She placed it infront of the headdress and poured it full of Tanais Valley wyne.<br>
<br>
Tonight your coronation continues a ritual passed<br>
down to us through the ages. A ritual of music and movement, a celebration of community and joy, for we are a family, united in sisterhood. We are the creators and our own creations, The words and the music, both singer and song. Our traditions stretch back to the great Gaia herself, mother of us all, a tradition of dance-- of music-- of sacrifice-- of blood.&quot;<br>
<br>
She handed the chalice of wyne to Ardyn.<br>
<br>
&quot;This symbolizes the blood of our Ancestors, the Sisters that have fallen before us. Sacrificed everything so we could have our freedom. Drink and be one with them.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>-:¦:- Yakut -:¦:-<BR>
~Northern Amazon Shamaness~<BR>
"Our focus is our unity. Our minds, creator of worlds."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a62a2a><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonqueenardyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Queen Ardyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#330000>(7/25/02 11:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/amznpardyn/images/jm3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The New Vasilissa</span><hr size=1> Ardyn drained the glass of wyne, licks her pink lips. Hands the chalice back.<br>
<br>
&lt;Yakut&gt;<br>
Yakut places the headdress on Ardyn's head with a smile.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hail to the Queen.&quot;<br>
<br>
The Shamaness saluted Ardyn.<br>
<br>
&lt;Ardyn&gt;<br>
<br>
Ardyn saluted Yakut in return.<br>
<br>
&lt;Yakut&gt;<br>
<br>
&quot;Today, the Nation rejoices in it's newest Queen. Vasilissa Ardyn!.&quot;<br>
<br>
She cheers and lets out a celebration cry.<br>
<br>
&quot;It is done.&quot; <p>-¤- Ardyn O'the Wind -¤-<BR>=ll=Amazon Queen of the Eurasian Steppes=ll=<BR>**Amazon Warrior Shamaness**<BR>"My friends...they have faith in you. I don't"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udaughterofshylock.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daughter of Shylock</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#330000>(7/26/02 12:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Atmah Cyane</span><hr size=1> A golden mist appeared and a ghost like figure appeared before both amazons. She smiled to both and then looked to Ardyn.<br>
<br>
~&quot;I knew I chose the right one.&quot;~<br>
<br>
Surely enough, standing before them was the First Cyane herself. The Atmah. The Ancient.<br>
<br>
~&quot;You'll do this Nation proud Ardyn. Keep your sisters in your heart. Fallen and living, they are apart of you forever.&quot;~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a62a2a><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonqueenardyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Queen Ardyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#330000>(7/26/02 10:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/amznpardyn/images/jm3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Atmah</span><hr size=1> Ardyn smiled and bowed her head in respect of the Atmah. She raised her head and saluted the Ancient.<br>
<br>
&quot;Efharisto, I am honored. I will help my sisters, serve my Nation and honor my Ancestors to the best of my ability.&quot;<br>
<br>
